The paper deals with a geometric optimization problem involving rectangles, which suggests that it could belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The use of algorithms and polynomial time solutions also suggests that it could belong to the data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. The paper also involves combinatorial optimization, which could place it in the sub-categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and game theory (cs.GT).
